# ============================================================
# AI Command Centre vault — .gitignore
# ============================================================
# Default posture: this is a PRIVATE repository.
# If you're taking parts public (build-in-public), scroll to the
# PUBLIC-REPO section at the bottom and uncomment what applies.
# ============================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# OS junk
# ------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / IDE
# ------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
*~
.#*

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Obsidian — ignore machine-specific state, keep shared config
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# The .obsidian/ folder contains both shareable things (plugin
# configs, hotkeys, themes) and machine-specific things (workspace
# layout, cache). Ignore only the machine-specific bits so that
# moving between laptops keeps your setup consistent.
.obsidian/workspace
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/cache
.obsidian/graph.json
.obsidian/plugins/*/data.json
.trash/

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Claude Code
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Keep .claude/commands/ committed (the slash commands are part of
# the system). Ignore user-specific overrides, sessions, and logs.
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/sessions/
.claude/*.log
.claude/*.cache
.claude/*.lock

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Secrets & env files
# ------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.key
*.pem
secrets/

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Large media — use external storage or Git LFS, never raw git
# ------------------------------------------------------------
*.mp4
*.mov
*.mkv
*.webm
*.avi
*.psd
*.ai
*.sketch
*.fig
*.xd
assets/raw/
assets/_staging/

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Temporary files
# ------------------------------------------------------------
*.tmp
*.temp
*.bak
*.backup
.~lock.*

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Private scratch space — never committed
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Safety valves for anything that doesn't belong in a scene's
# Notes section but you want to keep around locally.
notes/
scratchpad/
private/
_private/

# Any file suffixed with _private.md or .private.md is ignored
# everywhere in the vault. Useful for private variants of shared files.
**/*_private.md
**/*.private.md

# Git cannot ignore partial file content. If a scene's Notes section
# contains confidential material, either move it to /private/ or
# prefix the filename with _ to keep it local (see below).

# ============================================================
# PUBLIC-REPO ADDITIONS
# ============================================================
# UNCOMMENT the lines below if you're making this a public,
# build-in-public repository. Without these ignores, you'd be
# publishing client-confidential material, personal relationships,
# and strategic work across multiple campaigns.
# ============================================================

# --- Client work (Talk with Flavour scene, Nathan's character file) ---
# Nathan hasn't consented to having his wound/want/need sheet public.
characters/nathan.md
characters/restaurant-owner-archetype.md
campaigns/command-centre/chapters/*/scenes/02-talk-with-flavour-*.md
artifacts/*/02-talk-with-flavour-*.md

# --- Personal relationships ---
# Yuri's character file is deliberately under-drafted because her
# interior isn't yours to publish, even in skeleton form.
characters/yuri.md

# --- Sibling campaigns (keep only command-centre public) ---
# The command-centre campaign is the public playthrough. The others
# are strategic work that shouldn't leak to a public repo unless you
# consciously decide they should.
campaigns/yurika/
campaigns/the-guild/
campaigns/agency/

# --- In-progress scenes (convention-based) ---
# Git can't filter by YAML frontmatter status, but a convention works:
# prefix in-progress scene filenames with _ (e.g. _03-dacakegasm.md),
# then rename on conclude. The pattern below ignores underscored files.
# **/_*.md

# ============================================================
# Future additions
# ============================================================
# If you add scripts or code to the vault later (e.g. a Python tool
# for bulk operations on scene files), extend this file accordingly:
__pycache__/
*.pyc
node_modules/
dist/
build/